===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|hamor|lang=ang}} < {{proto|Germanic|hamara-|label=Germanic}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|hamer|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Hammer|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|hammare|lang=se}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈhæm.ə(ɹ)/}}, {{SAMPA|/"h{m.@(r)/}}
*: {{rhymes|æmə(r)}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈhæmɚ/}}, {{SAMPA|/"h{m@`/}}
*: {{audio|en-us-hammer.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[tool]] with a heavy [[head]] and a [[handle]] used for [[pounding]].
# A moving part of a firearm that strikes the firing pin to discharge a gun.
# {{anatomy}} The [[malleus]].
# {{music}} In a piano or dulcimer, a piece of wood covered in felt that strikes the string.
# {{sports}} A device made of a [[heavy]] steel [[ball]] attached to a length of [[wire]], and used for [[throw]]ing.
# {{curling}} The last [[rock]] in an [[end]].
# {{context|Ultimate Frisbee}} A frisbee throwing style in which the disc is held upside-down with a forehand grip and thrown above the head.

